{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7942fab4-b6a4-41e5-a57c-38a5dbecd74a","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Recursive wildcard glob — `**\\*.*` (line 9, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n**Impact: High.** The `**\\*.*` glob forces MSBuild to walk the *entire* directory tree on every evaluation. This gets dramatically worse as the repo grows. Use a targeted glob (e.g., specific extensions or a subdirectory) instead.\n\n---\n\n### 2. File I/O via property function (line 13, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n**Impact: Medium.** Calling `System.IO.File.ReadAllText` during evaluation is synchronous I/O on the critical path. Every evaluation (IDE load, restore, build) pays this cost. Prefer reading the file in a build target that runs only when needed.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deeply chained `<Import>` files (3 levels)\n```\ncsproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\n**Impact: Low–Medium.** Each import adds a file-open + parse + evaluate cycle during project evaluation. Three levels isn't catastrophic, but the chain pattern scales poorly and makes evaluation time grow linearly with depth. Flatten where possible.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Issue | File | Severity |\n|---|---|---|\n| `**\\*.*` recursive glob | `.csproj:9` | 🔴 High |\n| `File::ReadAllText` in property | `.csproj:13` | 🟡 Medium |\n| 3-level import chain | `imports/*` | 🟠 Low–Med |\n\nThe recursive glob is the biggest offender — it's the most common cause of slow IDE responsiveness in large repos. The property-function file read is the next priority to address.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9d9dba27-fa4a-4916-b617-6e6c5d4079a5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project.","outputTokens":525},"id":"8f908881-5881-4a1e-b393-a9fae685a033","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:11:32.013Z","parentId":"24966dad-8908-4789-908c-75642c7f3452"}
